What a gem! I absolutely LOVED this family owned spot! If you are looking for a fancy eatery, this isn't it.... This is more for the people looking for a local brunch spot that hits the typical american style eatery AND even better you have a Dominican/Puerto Rican Menu as well! The owner made all our food and was so happy doing so. The pancakes were perfect. One of my daughters tried the pineapple upside-down pancake because we read a previous review talkimg about how they were a must try! Did not disappoint! The coffee was great! The server was great! The food was great! There was meter parking right in front. It was super convenient. We will most definitely return when we visit Springfield again. Kudos to Felix!

This is a restaurant located close to Downtown Springfield in 67 Liberty Street. I got the pleasure to meet the owner he was very friendly. He takes pride on their food and service. They really go above and beyond for every customer visiting them.  Our waitress Annabel was very hospitable. She was friendly and attentive. We ordered two big breakfast and every plate came with 2 eggs, a choice of bacon or sausage and each dish was served with pancakes. My party and I ordered some tea, our teas arrived with lemon on the side and honey.  Overall the experience was wonderful, the food was fresh, the pancakes were fluffy and had really quality ingredients, every bite was delicious and the portions were generous. The owner allowed us to try the chocolate pancake...AMAZING food  Keep supporting local business and if you are in Springfield this is a most go!!!  Thanks again Felix and Annabel for been so hospitable. We will come back.

After a weekend convention in Springfield, whose theme was "World Hunger," we could not find a place to stop for breakfast after church. Almost all places near the Mass Mutual Center were closed, including our favorite standby, SUBWAY. As we were driving out toward the Interstate about to give up, we spotted Felix's. We parked right in front and read an inviting menu, with service until 2:00 p.m. I had the complete breakfast for $8.99. The over easy eggs were just right, the sausage was peppery and tasty, and the hash browns were light and non greasy, and the English Muffins were just right. Even the fresh orange slice on the plate was juicy. Coffee was average but we had had plenty of coffee at the hotel and convention that morning.

The food came out and we got 2 cinnamon bagel sandwiches & 1 sesame bagel sandwich. And no hash browns. We told them about the issues & they cooked one hash brown and brought it over. At that point, we gave up on fixing the order. I just want to emphasize that we had a 'very simple order' that they couldn't even get half right.  To top it off, we waited at the cash register for 10+ minutes while they tried to figure out how to work it. We didn't have enough patience left to find out if we got charged for the hash browns we never got.  Maybe this was an off-day for them, but we will not be going back.
